{
  "stem": "268.7",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The-- the allies were bombing like mad in-- in the last few days of war.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So I never got to-- to prove my-- my prowess of-- of-- of being a electrician, which was also a-- a good thing because I would have probably gotten severely disciplined, and probably [? got ?] beat up and killed, maybe.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But we did dig ditches again, trenches, anti-tanks, and, you know, went to town of Schoenbeck to clear rubbish and bombed-out houses.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And again, organizing came in handy.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I'd jump in the cellar, look for some-- sometimes we would find the jars of apples or tomatoes or sauerkraut, you know, in jars.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we would-- we would eat some and then suffer through it because you would-- you would have stomach problem, you know.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But-- but it-- it was a way of getting-- or carrots, anything we could find, just anything to eat.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "This took another-- this is March now of 1944.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "1944.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "March of 1944.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Schoenbeck.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was the-- the-- the camp that they sent-- that-- that I went from Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I'm trying to, you know, to kind of bring things to a conclusion because it's-- it's hard to-- to put everything, you know, on one tape.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I know I'm-- I'm skipping perhaps a-- a few things.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I'm trying to get to the important events, even though I remember small ones too.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And now, we in, as I said, March of 1944.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And obviously, the-- the front is nearing to-- to this town of Schoenbeck.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Schoenbeck, I didn't know until we start marching again, that it was right on-- at the-- on the Elbe River.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In fact, at the river, the town was one-- half of it one side, now half on the other side.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
